comment: Definitional property of the ` S.2 ` integral: for any function ` F ` there is a countable sequence ` g ` of simple functions less than ` F ` whose integrals converge to the integral of ` F ` . (This theorem is for the most part unnecessary in lieu of ~ itg2i1fseq , but unlike that theorem this one doesn't require ` F ` to be measurable.) (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 14-Aug-2014.)
